						<summary>

						

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Sōmēśvara Year: -</hi></p>						

						<p>This record registers a gift for providing two lamps to the temple of Tirunelvēliyoḍayadēva by Vāmaṇṇa, the brother-in-law <hi rend="italic">(maiduna)</hi> of Varadaṇṇa Daṇṇāyaka, the <hi rend="italic">śrīkaraṇa</hi> of the (Hoysaḷa) king, Vīrasōmēśvara-dēvarasa.</p>						

						<p>It is also recorded that out of the two gifted lamps, one was intended to be burnt in the sanctum sanctorum of the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
